{"type":"message","id":"5e562ae2","parentId":"6829cad3","timestamp":"2026-04-13T10:59:55.405Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to proceed. They said \"那就听你的 办吧\" which means \"let's do it your way.\" I need to figure out what they want me to do exactly. \n\nLooking back at the conversation, I suggested:\n1. 关掉 chrome 进程/标签页\n2. 给 vibesurf-1 限定内存上限\n3. 升级内存\n\nSince they said \"听你的\" (let's do it your way), they're likely referring to option 1 or 2. Let me ask which one they want to proceed with, or offer to do both practical ones (1 and 2).\n\n\nActually, \"听你的\" could mean they're leaving it up to me to decide. The most impactful action would be killing the excess chrome processes first—that'll immediately free up memory. But without knowing exactly which ones are safe to terminate, I should probably ask before proceeding. Though re-reading their message, they might just be agreeing with my analysis rather than asking me to take action right now."},{"type":"text","text":"那你想先做哪个？\n\n1. **清理 chrome 进程** — 释放内存，立即见效\n2. **给 vibesurf-1 限定内存上限** — 避免它和系统抢资源，但需要重启容器才能生效\n\n还是两个都来？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776077986290,"responseId":"062bffa282d6b770ddc900c44c70a293"}}
