{"type":"message","id":"f6a549c5","parentId":"01be2628","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:00:32.931Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, `killall -c chrome` might have killed them but the count shows 21. Let me check if new chrome processes were spawned or if the kill didn't work. Actually looking at the output, `killall -c chrome` seems to have returned \"done\" with no error but `pgrep -a chrome | wc -l` still shows 21. \n\nWait, `killall -c` is not the right flag. Let me check - actually `killall` doesn't have a `-c` flag. The output \"done\" is just from the echo. Let me re-examine.\n\nActually `killall` without a pid got the shell itself (PID 1 in the exec). \n\nThat can't be right. Let me check if chrome is still running."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jjgb7pwoov7b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pgrep -a chrome | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078027511,"responseId":"062bffcb8bc6f2ba836f7165004782da"}}
