{"type":"message","id":"f9c7f5a5","parentId":"bf2e1824","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:03:15.503Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to set a memory limit of 1.5GB for vibesurf-1. I need to update the container's memory limit. This requires updating the container's memory limit.\n\nThe command would be:\n`docker update --memory 1.5g --memory-swap 1.5g vibesurf-1`\n\nBut I should also set `--memory-swap` to the same value to prevent swap from being used excessively. Actually, if memory-swap is set to the same as memory, it means no swap. Let me think about this...\n\nActually, setting memory-swap to the same as memory means the container can't use swap at all. \n\nSetting memory and memory-swap to the same value works, but I need to account for shared memory too—vibesurf-1 already has a 4GB shmSize defined, so if I set the hard limit to 1.5GB, that shmSize would still be added on top. The safest approach is to set `--memory 1.5g --memory-swap 1.5g` to prevent swap usage entirely, and the user can always adjust if needed."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ejcurkkobjud_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker update --memory 1.5g --memory-swap 1.5g vibesurf-1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776078186569,"responseId":"062c006aff61555e05675fd4f0a8bd40"}}
