{"type":"message","id":"c26bb4dc","parentId":"0639a56e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T11:03:27.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"1610612736 bytes = 1.5GB. Both memory and memory swap are set to 1.5GB, which means no swap allowance (memory-swap = memory means no additional swap).\n\nBut wait - if memory-swap equals memory, that means no swap is allowed. This might cause OOM issues. Let me check the current docker update documentation. Actually, when memory-swap is set equal to memory, it means the container can't use any swap. This could be problematic if the container tries to use more than 1.5GB.\n\nActually, I should check - the default behavior is that memory-swap is the total amount of memory + swap. \n\nSo if memory is 1.5GB and memory-swap is 1.5GB, that means 0 swap. This is a valid configuration but might cause OOM kills. Let me verify it's applied correctly."},{"type":"text","text":"已更新。下次重启容器时生效（`--memory 1.5g --memory-swap 1.5g`）。\n\n验证：内存上限 = 1,610,612,736 bytes = **1.5GB**（无额外 swap）。\n\n**效果：** 容器重启后最多只能用 1.5GB，不会再把系统吃满。当然如果 1.5GB 不够用，浏览器页面多的时候可能会 OOM 被杀，到时候再调大或者继续清理都行。\n\n重启命令要我执行吗？还是先这样跑着看看？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776078197826,"responseId":"062c007632e8c081dff26f56a232788f"}}
